content: Fun rouge-like game although a short one. A nice mix of monsters and loot with a good blend of style, animation and music. It has the traditional rouge permadeath, but it's still relatively easy to finish the main story quest.
What is bound for wait a turn in this mobile version? I can't wait a turn like on other devices?

Would like to see an easier way to play caster, constantly switching to and out of a spell is absolutely tedious. Also, a way to shrink the borders so you aren't accidentally tabbing out constantly by hitting minimize functions on your phone. Ppl in the reviews are saying it isnt "balanced" without knowing what it means , this isn't a multiplayer game, this isn't World of warcraft, there are not multiplayer engagements or PvP functionality. The gameplay is fun and addictive that's that
Good game
Great simple Roguelike for Android. Runs smooth fun classes, and lots of skills to unlock. I really like the character sprites too.

Here's how to meet the enemy without getting hit first. Move one square in front of a door, with the enemy on the other side of the door. Now, click the door, and the enemy will approach you, while you stand still and get the first hit!! I know you guys will all want to shower me with money for this top secret, fantastic pro tip, but that's ok, I'm just too modest.
Still my favorite game to play just wish they could add more things to it from time to time.
Fun game. Loved it. How about a sequel?
replyContent: Hello, glad you enjoy it. No plans atm for a sequel but I'll keep your suggestion in mind.

content: Excellent game but get ready to die! Survive the dungeons.. find loot and equip yourself for a fight.. each room a potential treasure or room of doom! Find the store keep quickly and upgrade your gear.. potions and food.. Are you up for the challenge? Why not find out by playing Quest of Dungeons..

Its a fun game for about 5 minutes. There isnt really much balancing and picking up a different looking item just to find out its named, "weak(insert weapon/armor/shield)" is lack luster. Gold balancing is another issue. Picking up the increasingly rare gems doesnt feel worth it, since you could pick up a shiny rock or a triple emerald quartz square diamond and they both sell for 15 gold, while the items the shop keeper offers are low tier items that cost 10k or more. Overall its a 4 chicken feet

The game itself is great. It's strategic, the different classes give good flavors, it looks and feels nice, etc. More than worthy of the 2 dollar price tag. However, after upgrading my phone to the LG G3, sometimes floors would lack bosses or a shop. Sometimes doors required two keys as well, although I don't know if that was a bug or just something I never ran into before. It did start freezing on me, but deleting and re-downloading the app fixed the problem. Pretty good overall.

I used to play a game on my Sega Genesis called Fatal Labyrinth. Much like this game, you had one shot to make it through. This is a nice take on that game, and really gives me that classic feeling of nostalgia. Very well-done. I've died a lot playing this, and I don't even care. Keep up the great work. I'll be recommending this game to IGN.
Good game

Otherwise fantastic app. There are so many rogue likes on mobile,  but most are very amateur, with balance issues. This is the best roguelike app, well worth the price. Would really appreciate being able to track records or best runs.
Sticks around in the background and drains my battery. Gets old fast, not much of a challenge.
I now own the game on my phone and computer.  A great challenging way to pass the time!

Game is production ready (why it gets 2 stars)  but did not enjoy this game. the learning curve is not satisfying, the game play is slow and doesn't promote strategy, doesnt involve risk/reward. Try Pixel Dungeon- gameplay speed isn't boring, risk/reward makes replayable, and map is way more navigable. Pixel Dungeon learning curve is short, promotes strategy, rather than this game, which just calls for you to play more. This game you will win but only by making right decisions, those decisions are learned.
Best rogue like I tried on Android so far. Reminds me of Dungeons of Dreadmor Wish levelling had actual skill points.
Like the good arcade games like at the old arcades in the 90ds and 80ds

If you enjoy perma-death dungeon crawlers then you won't be disappointed. Only two complaints I have are: 1) if you are using a character with a bow and you miss tapping an enemy you will run towards where you tapped likely taking damage on the way and 2) when an enemy steals an item they don't drop it on death (lost a doom key this way). Other than those minor complaints it is an excellent game.
Old school - death means you start over. There are only 7 levels to beat, but you can choose different character classes.
I'd love to see more people playing it. Supporting good developers and making the Android marketplace better. Thank you

While this game is fine, there isn't much to it, especially compared to similar products. While I appreciate the lighter difficulty,  it can become monotonous quickly, even on harder difficulties, and the general lack of things to do besides tap monsters and the environment leave the game feeling empty. Being able to find hidden doors or having a hunger system or simply changing the enemy AI a bit so every enemy doesn't just charge blindly at you would go a long way in really making this game shine.

The gameplay is fun and has a good level of challenge to it, with the ability to choose harder or easier difficulties. There are 4 classes to choose from, but I feel as though only 1 class, the Assassin, is consistently good. It can avoid damage by attacking at a range. The wizard is powerful, but it runs out mana too quick. The phone version lacks much of the info the tablet version has.
It isnt a bad game, just isn't my thing. But I played for 10 minutes and decided to get q refund. It wont refund me, I am not tripping too hard but I thought I would mention it

I hate hate hate hate hate the permanent death!!! You should be able to pick if you want to use it and also only 1 save too good solid game aside from those things it's good get it and I hope you add more classes

Love this game it says its like a 16bit turn based game and it is exactly that. It doesn't "save" your progress per say, what I mean by that is when you die there is no return to last checkpoint, instead you restart the game. I fell like that makes the player use more skill and not act like they are playing a hack and slash RPG. And that's why I give this 5.stars.

Charming little roguelike, not overly complex and with a save feature that makes it perfect to play whenever I can spare a few minutes. Interface by no means is bad but might benefit from a few minor tweaks. Developer support fast & helpful.
